value.value: An indication that a treatment or therapy was changed or discontinued because it is no longer clinically beneficial to the subject or patient, based on the primary therapeutic objective for which it is being administered and assessed. (Trial Design and Objectives for Castration-Resistant Prostate Cancer: Updated Recommendations From the Prostate Cancer Clinical Trials Working Group 3. Scher HI, Morris MJ, Stadler WM, et al.; Prostate Cancer Clinical Trials Working Group 3. J Clin Oncol. 2016 Apr 20;34(12):1402-18.)
The total amount of sleep time from sleep onset to sleep offset, determined by summing the N1 sleep, N2 sleep, N3 sleep, and REM sleep durations.
A relative measurement (percentage) of the time spent asleep (N1 sleep + N2 sleep + N3 sleep + REM sleep) to the total time spent in bed.
A measurement of the sum of durations of wakefulness episodes throughout the night, not including the wakefulness before sleep onset.

label.value: N1 Sleep to Total Sleep Time Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of N1 sleep time compared to total sleep time. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: N2 Sleep to Total Sleep Time Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of N2 sleep time compared to total sleep time. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: N3 Sleep to Total Sleep Time Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of N3 sleep time compared to total sleep time. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: REM to Total Sleep Time Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of REM sleep time compared to total sleep time. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.
The maximum height change between the wave and the equilibrium point of a stimulus-response waveform.
Any surgical procedure performed on nervous system tissue.
The time duration between the stimulus and the maximum response.
The determination of the amount of N-acetyl aspartate in a biological specimen.
The determination of the amount of myo-inositol in a biological specimen.
The determination of the amount of glutamate and glutamine in a biological specimen.
An assessment of the anatomic response (based on changes in size of anatomic structures) of the disease to the therapy.

label.value: Metabolite Ratio for AUC Infinity Observed

value.value: The ratio of AUC infinity observed for the metabolite to the AUC infinity observed for the parent analyte.

label.value: Metabolite Ratio for AUC Infinity Predicted

value.value: The ratio of AUC infinity predicted for the metabolite to the AUC infinity predicted for the parent analyte.

label.value: Metabolite Ratio AUC Last Nonzero Concentration

value.value: The ratio of AUC to last nonzero concentration for the metabolite to the AUC to last nonzero concentration for the parent analyte.

label.value: Metabolite Ratio for AUC Dosing Interval

value.value: The ratio of AUC over dosing interval (TAU) for the metabolite to the AUC over dosing interval (TAU) for the parent analyte.
The ratio of metabolite maximum concentration to the parent analyte maximum concentration.
General term for hemodialysis, plasmapheresis, blood transfusions, and related procedures involving autologous removal, alteration, and replacement of patients' blood or blood components.

label.value: Volume of Distribution Steady State Observed by Fraction of Dose Absorbed

value.value: The volume of distribution at steady state based on the observed CLST for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, divided by the fraction of dose absorbed.

label.value: Volume of Distribution Steady State Predicted by Fraction of Dose Absorbed

value.value: The volume of distribution at steady state based on the predicted CLST for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, divided by the fraction of dose absorbed.

label.value: Volume of Distribution Steady State Observed by Unbound Drug

value.value: The volume of distribution at steady state based on the observed CLST for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, divided by the fraction of unbound drug.

label.value: Volume of Distribution Steady State Predicted by Unbound Drug

value.value: The volume of distribution at steady state based on the predicted CLST for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, divided by the fraction of unbound drug.

label.value: Volume of Distribution Steady State Observed by Bound Drug

value.value: The volume of distribution at steady state based on the observed CLST for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, divided by the fraction of bound drug.

label.value: Volume of Distribution Steady State Predicted by Bound Drug

value.value: The volume of distribution at steady state based on the predicted CLST for a substance administered by extravascular dosing, divided by the fraction of bound drug.

label.value: Fractional Excretion from T1 to T2

value.value: The fraction of the administered dose that is recovered from the specimen type, over the interval between T1 and T2.

label.value: Area Under the Curve Ratio Infinity Predicted

value.value: The ratio of two AUC infinity predicted values.

label.value: Area Under the Curve Ratio Infinity Observed

value.value: The ratio of two AUC infinity observed values.
The determination of the ratio of one Cmax value compared to another Cmax value. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.
Systematic investigation into the role that nutrition plays in cancer.
The determination of the ratio of one Cmax value compared to a Cmin value. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Observed Volume of Distribution of Absorbed Fraction for Unbound Drug

value.value: The volume of distribution associated with the terminal slope following extravascular administration divided by the fraction of dose absorbed, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration and corrected for unbound drug.
Any immunotherapy that targets, or is restricted to, a specific anatomical location.

A person of mixed race, whose ancestry is from one or more of the naturalized racial groups of Southern Africa (typically Western European, South Asian, or Southeastern Asian) and one or more of the indigenous Southern African peoples.
The quantity of fresh gas that enters the alveoli during inspiration.
A subjective description of the menstrual flow rate during a menstrual cycle.
The number of days during which menses is expelled from the uterus.
A description of how an individual's menstrual cycle conforms to a consistent temporal pattern.
An indication as to whether the female subject has had an induced abortion procedure.
An indication as to whether the subject has delivered live-born offspring.
The study of how nutritional needs change with aging.
Administration within the mandible.
Any cell with a single nucleus found in the bone marrow, for example lymphocytes, monocytes, mesenchymal stem cells and hematopoietic progenitor cells.

label.value: Open Label for Treatment And Double Blind to Dose

value.value: A study in which the therapeutic treatment is open label but the dosing information of the investigational medicinal product (IMP) is double-blinded.
An increase in size, volume, or quantity in comparison to nadir.
An increase in size, volume, or quantity in comparison to a previous state that was enlarged from nadir.
A clinical trial or treatment setting in which the therapy of interest is considered induction therapy.
A clinical trial or treatment setting in which the therapy of interest is considered mobilization therapy.
